# Eval Sync

When a change to `backend/` alters observable behavior, update or add corresponding evals in `evals/` in the same task. Do not wait for the user to ask.

## What counts as observable behavior change

- New, removed, or renamed fields in models (`models.py`)
- Changed prompt structure, output schema, or LLM call logic (`llm.py`)
- Modified pipeline flow, early exits, or branching (`pipeline.py`)
- Changed search query construction or result handling (`search.py`)
- New or changed API endpoints or response shapes (`main.py`)
- Changed config values that affect defaults or thresholds (`config.py`)

## What to update in evals

| Change type | Eval action |
|---|---|
| New field or output | Add assertions for the new field in relevant unit tests |
| Removed field | Remove or update assertions that reference it |
| Changed verdict/score logic | Update expected values in unit tests and golden dataset entries if needed |
| New pipeline branch or early exit | Add a unit test covering that path |
| Changed prompt or rubric | Update quality eval expected dimensions and judge criteria (`judges.py`) |
| New endpoint | Add an E2E test exercising it |

## What does NOT require eval changes

- Pure refactors with identical inputs/outputs
- Comment or docstring edits
- Dependency version bumps with no API change
